MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
Top rap acts, including several who threatened to boycott the Grammy ceremonies 
today, are planning to attend an MTV-hosted post-Grammys party tonight. 
According to an MTV spokeswoman, nominees J.J. Fad, Jazzy Jeff &amp; the Fresh 
Prince, Salt-N-Pepa and Kool Moe Dee are among those expected at the party, 
which will feature a rap and scratch jam by those and other performers, 
including Ice-T. The location of the private party, which will be videotaped 
for use on MTV Music News segments and on the "Yo! MTV Raps" series, is not 
being revealed to the public. Shauna Snow 
